info.title: Etsy Order: {{26.receipt_id}}
info.description:
Hey {{3.choices[].message.content}}! Thank you for your purchase. We're looking forward to creating something special with you.

This form helps us gather as much relevant information as possible to best bring your imagination to life. 

Thank you for helping us make your commission as amazing as possible.

items.title: Reference Images
items.description: The first section is for your reference images. Please upload any references to the three batches below. If you upload images to a batch, please provide details on what makes those images important.

items.title: Image Batch One:
items.description: Please upload your first batch of images here: {{32.shareLink}}

items.title: Please give context to the attached Images in batch one:
Image Batch Two:
items.description: Please upload your second batch of images here: {{33.shareLink}}

items.title: Please give context to the attached Images in batch two:
Image Batch Three:
items.description: Please upload your third batch of images here: {{34.shareLink}}

items.title: Please give context to the attached Images in batch three:
Essential Questions:
items.description: Any questions in this section are essential to fully understanding your vision

items.title: Character Basics
items.description: Please provide a description of the character, including their name, age, gender, and any significant features. Additionally, please include their body type, hair color and style, eye color, and skin tone as is applicable.

items.title: Extra Questions:
items.description: These questions will help with understanding your vision, but are not required if you would prefer to skip them.

items.title: Personality:
items.description: What is the character’s personality like? Are there any specific traits or quirks that you would like to be reflected in the artwork?

items.title: Clothing and Accessories:
items.description: What kind of clothing and accessories does your character wear?

items.title: Special Requests:
items.description: Are there any unique elements, features, or requests that you would like to include in your commission, which haven’t been covered in the previous questions?

mapper.html:
Hey {{3.choices[].message.content}},

Thank you for your order, and for supporting small businesses!
This is just the initial email to say hi and collect your commission details, which you can fill out at this link:

{{1.responderUri}}

Please remember, that the more information you can provide us, the better we'll be able to understand your vision.

Thank you for the information, and we look forward to creating something wonderful!

Sincerely,
Adam, Founder of Wattle Art Creations
mapper.subject: Thanks for your Etsy Order #{{26.receipt_id}}

info.title: Etsy Order: {{26.receipt_id}}
info.description:
Hey {{3.choices[].message.content}}, welcome back! Repeat clients such as yourself are so valuable to us, and I can't thank you enough for trusting us with another piece. 

You probably know the process by now, but this form helps us gather as much relevant information as possible to best bring your imagination to life. 

As a repeat client there's a couple of extra questions to help tailor your experience this time around.

Thank you for helping us make your commission as amazing as possible.

items.title: Looking back, how do you feel about your previous experience?
Do you have any specific feedback related to your previous commissioning experience?
Would you like the same artist as last time?

options.value: Yes - Assign me the same artist
No - Assign me a new artist

Hey {{3.choices[].message.content}},

Welcome back, and can I just say that you look absolutely fantastic today?

Return customers such as yourself are the only reason we can do what we do. Your continued support is deeply appreciated:

You probably know the drill by now, but here's the form where we'll gather any essential information for the piece:

{{108.responderUri}}

Please remember, that the more information you can provide us, the better we'll be able to understand your vision.

Thank you for your continued support and trust.

Sincerely,
Adam, Founder of Wattle Art Creations
